Package com.osiris.dyml

Class DreamYaml

java.lang.Object
com.osiris.dyml.DreamYaml
public class DreamYaml
extends java.lang.Object
The in-memory representation of the full yaml file that contains all of the default and loaded modules.

  • Method Details

    • load

      public DreamYaml load()
      Loads the file into memory by parsing it into modules(DYModule). Creates a new file if it didn't exist already. You can return the list of modules with getAllLoaded(). Remember, that this refreshes all modules values.

    • save

      public DreamYaml save()
      Saves the current modules and their values to the provided yaml file. Everything gets overwritten and stuff that couldn't be parsed into modules gets removed from the file. Missing modules in the file, get created using their default values. See DYModule.setDefValues(List) and UtilsForModules.createUnifiedList(List, List) for more details. It's recommended to keep load() and save() timely close to each other, so the user can't change the values in the meantime.
      Throws:
      NotLoadedException

    • add

      public DYModule add​(DYModule module) throws java.lang.Exception
      Adds a module to the list, which will get parsed and written to file by save(). Doing changes to this modules values and saving them, will affect the original yaml file.
      Parameters:
      module - module to add.
      Returns:
      the added module.
      Throws:
      NotLoadedException - if the yaml file has not been loaded once yet
      DuplicateKeyException - if another module with the same keys already exists
      java.lang.Exception

    • remove

      public void remove​(DYModule module)
      Removes a module the module. If you call save() after this, the module should also be removed from the yaml file.
      Parameters:
      module - the module to remove.

    • getAllLoaded

      public java.util.List<DYModule> getAllLoaded()
      Returns a list containing all loaded modules. It is a temporary list which gets refreshed every time load() is called. Its modules, do not contain default values.

    • getLastLoadedModule

      public DYModule getLastLoadedModule()

    • getAllAdded

      public java.util.List<DYModule> getAllAdded()
      Returns a list containing all currently added modules. Modules should only be added by add(String...) and never by this lists own add() method. This list is not affected by load(), unlike the 'loaded modules' list, which can be returned by getAllLoaded().
